        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. One hundred passengers board a plane with exactly 100 seats. The first passenger takes a seat at random. The second passenger takes his own seat if it is available, otherwise he takes at random a seat among the available ones. The third passenger takes his own seat if it is available, otherwise he takes at random a seat among the available ones. This process continues until all the 100 passengers have boarded the plane. What is the probability that the last passenger takes his own seat? "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                141,
                234,
                889,
                338
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2. Assume a sequence of random variables "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "converges in distribution to a random variable "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\{ N _ { t } , t \\ge 0 \\}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a set of positive integer-valued random variables, which is independent of ( "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ") and converges in probability to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "as "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "t \\to \\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X _ { N _ { t } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "converges in distribution to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "as "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "t \\to \\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
